I'll start by executing the file_operations_reader tool to read the input data as the first step in our pipeline.

<tool_call>file_operations_reader
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Since the file_operations_reader timed out, I'll try an alternative tool for reading the input file. I'll use the file_operations_scanner which also has file reading capabilities.

<tool_call>file_operations_scanner
{
  "source": "data/input.json", 
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now that we've successfully read the input data, I'll proceed with the next step in our pipeline: filtering the data. I'll use the data_processing_filter tool for this stage.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {
    "filter_type": "basic",
    "output_format": "json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

Since the data_processing_validator requires data_processing_parser as a dependency, I'll first execute the parser to prepare the data for validation.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Now that the data is parsed, I can proceed with the validation step using the data_processing_validator tool.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {
    "validation_rules": "default",
    "format": "json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

            With the data successfully validated, I'll now proceed to the transformation stage using the data_processing_transformer tool. According to the workflow plan, this tool also requires data_processing_parser as a dependency, which we've already executed.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {
    "transformation_type": "standard",
    "output_format": "json"
  }
}
</tool_call>

                        Since we've already executed the data_processing_parser (which is the only dependency for data_processing_aggregator), I'll now execute the aggregator to prepare for the final analysis step.

<tool_call>data_processing_aggregator
{
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
